= AutoRadio version 1.0 =
http://autoradiobc.sourceforge.net/

Radio automation software. Simple to use, starting from digital audio
files manages on-air broadcasting over a radio-station or
web-radio. The main components are:

    * Player (Xmms): plays all your media files and send digital sound
      to an audio device or audio server
 
    * Scheduler: real time manager for emission of special audio files
      like jingles, spots, playlist and programs; interact with player
      like supervisor User

    * inteface: WEB interface to monitor the player and scheduler and
      admin the schedules for the complete control over your station
      format

Developed with Python, Django, Xmms it works in an production enviroment


FEATURES
--------

 * manage ogg, mp3, wav and other media file format
 * it's designed as client server
 * do not averlap schedules: anticipate, postone or delete
 * comples rules for schedule and period schedule
 * player is monitored by web interface

REQUIRES
--------

autoradio requires:

mutagen
muatgen version > 1.17
http://code.google.com/p/mutagen/

at this time (11-09-2009) you can obtain it only with svn:
svn checkout http://mutagen.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ mutagen
You can get also some tar and rpm from autoradio project home page 

django
http://www.djangoproject.com/
I suggest Django 1.1

pyxmms
http://people.via.ecp.fr/~flo/index.en.xhtml

cherrypy2
Summary     : A pythonic, object-oriented web development framework
URL         : http://www.cherrypy.org/
Thera are incompatibility from cherrypy version 2 and 3
If you have a recent distribution and have installed egg files for
cherrypy2 compatibility package (like Fedora) autoradio try to get
the correct version of cherrypy
Otherwise you have to patch xmmsweb.py


configobj
Summary     : Config file reading, writing, and validation
URL         : http://www.voidspace.org.uk/python/configobj.html

xmms
http://www.xmms.org/


HOW TO INSTALL
--------------

>>>>> Easy way:
You can run autoradio daemon and web server from root distributed directory:

change your preferred language and other preference in autoradio.cfg 

./init.sh

You have to respond to some question to setup database.

This star daemon autoradiod (that launch xmms and xmmsweb) 
and webserver on port 8080
xmmsweb respond on port 8888

You have to use a browser pointing to localhost:8080


>>>>> Installed way:
python setup.py install

make and go in your preferred working writable directory
modify /etc/autoradio/autoradio-site.cfg or
copy it in your working directory with name autoradio.cfg and modify
specify your personal settings for installed files
if you want you can set global user setting coping configuration file in
~/.autoradio.cfg

after:

django-admin.py syncdb --settings=settings --pythonpath=/usr/lib/python<your python version number>/site-packages/autoradio
autoradiod run
autoradioweb run

You can run autoradiod and xmms in one host and autoradioweb in other if
you use client server DB like mysql and specify where autoradiod is
running in .cfg files

For a pubblic web server do not use django internal web server; use
apache instead
http://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/howto/deployment/modpython/#howto-deployment-modpython


HOW IT WORKS
------------

in xmms playlist you need a queue of media for a minumun of some hours
and for this you have to program some playlist
xmms cannot stay stopped or paused (if stopped it will be started, if paused it stay paused) for a corret work.
When time will be right jingle, programs and spots will be placed in playlist the first position after the last file inserted before by autoradiod 


